       State Map

                   Asotin County

                                          Click a number on the map below
                                                for launch details.

                          asotin.gif (86505 bytes)

   Up Arrow to Map   1. Chief Timothy State Park

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City: Clarkston


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Dumpstation
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  4 Concrete Ramp
                                  2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  40 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Clarkston, W on US 12 8 mi; R at park entrance sign.
        Site Description:

        New floats are needed for the loading floats. Logs and other wood
        debris can accumulate at the boat ramp. Users should check the
        launch lanes prior to launching or loading. The dump station is
        presently not working. A new dump station should be installed soon.
        The park manager is not sure of the dump station installation at
        this time.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Hell's Canyon Marina

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: Clarkston Port of
        Nearest City: Clarkston


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Clarkston on US12 (Bridge St.), go W to SR128 junction; N on SR
        128 (15th St) .1 mi; before crossing Red Wolf Bridge, turn L and go
        .1 mi. Marina and ramp will be on left.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp consists of solid concrete slab in good condition, 60
        degree channels to clean ramp, and a moderate slope. Hell's Canyon
        Resort manages the marina which offers boat moorage, a convenience/
        tackle store, and a restaurant. Parking for the ramp is across the
        street. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Greenbelt Trail

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Clarkston
        Nearest City: Clarkston


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  2 Concrete Ramp
                                  1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     34 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  31 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        In Clarkston, follow Hwy 12 (Bridge St) to E end of town, turn L on
        5th St. Go N 1 block; turn R on Fair St. Follow Fair St.
        Site Description:

        The ramp consists of a solid concrete slab in good condition with a
        moderate grade. Abrupt edges have developed on both sides of the
        ramp. This site is the trailhead to the Greenbelt Trail which
        provides users with a paved trail for walking, running, and biking.
        A fee is charged for the use of the boat ramp ($2.00). Near the boat
        ramp is a small area and the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Resources
        Management Office.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Swallows Park

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Clarkston
        Nearest City: Clarkston


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 4 Concrete Ramp
                                 3 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     7 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 62 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Clarkston, S on SR 129 2 mi; boat ramp area is past swimming
        area on E side of SR 129.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp concrete is in good condition. Moderate grade.
        Protected by a jettied basin. Swallows Park also has large lawn
        areas, picnic tables, swimming beach, paved walking trails, paved
        bike trail, and several restrooms. A fee is charged to use the boat
        ramp ($2.00).


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Chief Looking Glass Park

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: Asotin Parks & Rec Dept
        Nearest City: Asotin


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Dumpstation
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  1 Loading Float
                                  2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     24 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  47 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Clarkston, S on SR 129 5 mi to Asotin; L at entrance to Chief
        Looking Glass Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has chipped planks, moderate grade, and is protected
        in a basin away from the river current. Chief Looking Glass Park
        also offers a large lawn area, play equipment, swimming beach,
        basketball court, picnic tables, BBQ grills, and a public phone.
        This park is also located next to Asotin High School's football and
        baseball fields. A touring paddle boat is moored next to the boat
        ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. Asotin Slough Habitat Management Unit

        Waterbody: Lower Granite Lake
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Clarkston
        Nearest City: Asotin


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water levels would prevent the use of this boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        In Asotin, S on 2nd St; L on unmarked gravel Rd across from softball
        fields, follow Rd to ramp parking area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is located at moderate to swift river current. The mid
        to lower ramp is buried underneath a significant amount of sand
        deposited by the Snake River. No designated disabled parking. No
        overnight camping at this site. The parking area is rough and
        uneven. At its present condition, this ramp can be used for hand
        launching vessels. A softball complex is located across the road
        from the boat ramp area.


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Heller Bar

        Waterbody: Snake River
        Site Manager: US Bureau of Land Management
        Nearest City: Asotin


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water levels would prevent the use of this ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Asotin, S on Snake River Rd 22 mi; at Restaurant, turn L to
        parking area, follow paved Rd N 400 ft.
        Site Description:

        Some undermining erosion has developed on the upper portion of the
        ramp due to high river levels. The concrete planks are in good
        condition. No designated disabled parking. The closest 20 parking
        spaces to the boat ramp are in good condition, however, the further
        spaces are rough and uneven. A 14 day camping limit is enforced in
        the parking area. This recreation site is cooperatively managed by
        the U.S. Forest Service, the Bureau of Land Management, and the
        WDFW.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. R. Boogan

        Waterbody: Grande Ronde River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City: Asotin


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water levels would prevent the use of this ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Asotin, S on SR 129 31.6 mi to S side of Grande Ronde River
        Bridge; R to enter parking area by bridge.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is constructed with rough rock with a moderate grade
        on a moderate to swift river current. Flood waters have stripped the
        parking area and boat ramp of the smaller gravel. Therefore, these
        areas are very rough and uneven. No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. SR129 Gravel Pit (DOT) - Grand Ronde

        Waterbody: Grande Ronde River
        Site Manager: Transportation Dept of
        Nearest City: Asotin


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high water levels would prevent the use of the ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Asotin, S on SR 129 31.6 mi to S side of Grande Ronde River
        bridge; ramp located at N end of parking lot.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade and is located on a
        section of the Grand Ronde River that has a moderate to swift
        current. This site is more suitable for launching boats by hand or
        smaller motor boats. No designated disabled parking. No sign to
        indicate the location of this ramp. No sign to indicate the owner or
        managing agency of this site. Gravel storage piles share the parking
        area.



